# Adding New Features - Step-by-Step Guide

## Overview

This guide walks through adding a new feature to the Weighsoft Backend API, following all established patterns and conventions.

## Step 1: Create the Model

Create `app/Models/MyFeature.php`:

```php
<?php

namespace App\Models;

use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Factories\HasFactory;
use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Model;
use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\SoftDeletes;

class MyFeature extends Model
{
    use SoftDeletes;

    protected $table = 'my_features';
    
    protected $fillable = [
        'name',
        'description',
        'company_id',
        'site_id',
        // ... all fillable fields
    ];

    // Relationships
    public function company(): BelongsTo
    {
        return $this->belongsTo('App\Models\Company');
    }
}
```

## Step 2: Create the Controller

Create `app/Http/Controllers/MyFeatureController.php`:

```php
<?php

namespace App\Http\Controllers;

use App\Models\MyFeature;
use Illuminate\Http\JsonResponse;
use Illuminate\Http\Request;
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Validator;

class MyFeatureController extends JwtAuthController
{
    private MyFeature $model;

    public function __construct() {
        parent::__construct();  // REQUIRED
        $this->model = new MyFeature();
    }

    public function index(): JsonResponse
    {
        $companyId = $this->user->company_id;
        
        // Role-based filtering
        if (!$companyId || ($this->user->role_id == 1) || ($this->user->role_id == 2)) {
            $items = $this->model::all();
        } else {
            $items = $this->model::where('company_id', $companyId)->get();
        }
        
        return response()->json($items);
    }

    public function store(Request $request): JsonResponse
    {
        $item = $request->all();
        
        // Validation
        $validator = Validator::make($item, [
            'name' => 'required',
            'description' => 'required'
        ]);

        if ($validator->fails()) {
            return response()->json($validator->errors(), 422);
        }
        
        // Set defaults
        if (!isset($item['field'])) {
            $item['field'] = '';
        }
        
        // Create
        $feature = $this->model->create($item);
        return response()->json($feature);
    }

    public function show($id): JsonResponse
    {
        $item = $this->model->find($id);
        
        if (!$item) {
            return response()->json(['message' => 'Item not found'], 404);
        }
        
        return response()->json($item);
    }

    public function update(Request $request, $id): JsonResponse
    {
        $item = $request->all();
        
        // Validation
        $validator = Validator::make($item, [
            'name' => 'required',
            'description' => 'required'
        ]);

        if ($validator->fails()) {
            return response()->json($validator->errors(), 422);
        }
        
        $feature = $this->model->find($id);
        if (!$feature) {
            return response()->json(['status' => false, 'message' => 'Item not found'], 404);
        }
        
        // Set defaults
        $item['field'] = $item['field'] ?: '';
        
        $feature->update($item);
        return response()->json($feature);
    }

    public function destroy($id): JsonResponse
    {
        $item = $this->model->find($id);

        if (!$item) {
            return response()->json(['status' => false, 'message' => 'Item not found'], 404);
        }

        $item->delete();
        return response()->json(['status' => true]);
    }
}
```

## Step 3: Create the Migration

Create migration file in `database/migrations/`:

```php
<?php

use Illuminate\Database\Migrations\Migration;
use Illuminate\Database\Schema\Blueprint;
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Schema;

class CreateMyFeaturesTable extends Migration
{
    public function up()
    {
        Schema::create('my_features', function (Blueprint $table) {
            $table->id();
            $table->string('name');
            $table->text('description')->nullable();
            $table->unsignedBigInteger('company_id')->nullable();
            $table->unsignedBigInteger('site_id')->nullable();
            // ... more columns
            $table->timestamps();
            $table->softDeletes();
        });
    }

    public function down()
    {
        Schema::dropIfExists('my_features');
    }
}
```

Run migration:
```bash
php artisan migrate
```

## Step 4: Add the Route

Add to `routes/api.php`:

```php
Route::group([], function () {
    // ... existing routes
    
    Route::resource('myfeature', 'MyFeatureController');
});
```

## Step 5: Create Service (If Needed)

If the feature has complex business logic, create `app/Services/MyFeatureService.php`:

```php
<?php

namespace App\Services;

use App\Models\MyFeature;
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\DB;

class MyFeatureService
{
    public function getMyFeatures($companyId, $siteId, $filters): array
    {
        // Complex query logic
        $sql = "SELECT ... FROM my_features WHERE ...";
        $data = DB::select($sql, $parameters);
        $count = DB::selectOne("SELECT count(1) as count FROM my_features WHERE ...", $filterParams);
        
        return [$data, $count->count];
    }
    
    public function insertMyFeature($data)
    {
        // Complex insert logic
        DB::insert("INSERT INTO my_features (...) VALUES (...)", $params);
        return $this->getLastUpdatedItem();
    }
}
```

Then inject into controller:

```php
public function __construct(MyFeatureService $service) {
    parent::__construct();
    $this->model = new MyFeature();
    $this->service = $service;
}
```

## Step 6: Handle UUIDs (If Using UUIDs)

If the feature uses UUIDs:

### In Model
```php
// UUIDs are handled at database level, not in model
```

### In Controller/Service
```php
// Querying
$item = MyFeature::whereRaw("id = UUID_TO_BIN(?, TRUE)", [$id])
    ->first(["my_features.*", DB::raw("BIN_TO_UUID(id, TRUE) as id2")]);

if (!empty($item)) {
    $item['id'] = $item['id2'];
    unset($item['id2']);
}

// Inserting
DB::insert("INSERT INTO my_features (id, ...) VALUES (UUID_TO_BIN(UUID(), true), ...)", $params);
```

## Checklist for New Features

- [ ] Model created with `$fillable` array
- [ ] Model uses `SoftDeletes` if needed
- [ ] Controller extends `JwtAuthController`
- [ ] Controller calls `parent::__construct()`
- [ ] Controller validates requests
- [ ] Controller handles not found (404)
- [ ] Controller returns JSON responses
- [ ] Controller uses role-based filtering
- [ ] Route added to `routes/api.php`
- [ ] Migration created and run
- [ ] Service created if complex logic needed
- [ ] UUID handling implemented if using UUIDs
- [ ] Database transactions used for multi-step operations
- [ ] Error handling implemented

## Common Patterns Reference

### Pattern: Simple CRUD
- See: `CompanyController`, `SiteController`
- No service needed, direct model operations

### Pattern: Complex Business Logic
- See: `WeighingHeadersController` with `WeighingHeaderService`
- Service handles complex queries and operations

### Pattern: UUID Primary Keys
- See: `weighingHeaders`, `weighingTransactions`
- Use `UUID_TO_BIN()` / `BIN_TO_UUID()` functions

### Pattern: Soft Delete with Reason
- See: `deleteWithReason()` methods
- Custom route: `Route::post('resource/{id}/delete', [Controller::class, 'deleteWithReason']);`

## Step 6: Update Versions and Commit

**CRITICAL: After completing any changes, you MUST:**

1. **Update version numbers** in:
   - `build.bat` - Increment `set version=0.10.X`
   - `build.sh` - Increment `version=0.10.X`

2. **Commit all changes** with a descriptive message:
   ```bash
   git add .
   git commit -m "[Feature] Description of changes

   - Change 1
   - Change 2
   - Version updated to 0.10.X"
   ```

See `09-version-control-commits.mdc` for detailed version and commit workflow.

